Friday Olokor and Peter Dada a civil rights organisation, YIAGA Africa, has expressed optimism that Nigeria will witness higher turnout of voters in subsequent elections if the governorship election in Ondo State is as transparent as that of Edo State. YIAGA Africa also revealed that it had trained 646 observers for the Ondo governorship election. The organisation said apart from setting a new template for elections in Nigeria, Edo poll would remain a testament that votes could count in Nigerian elections “if institutions are given the opportunity to perform their functions without interference and can deliver credible and nonviolent elections.” Executive Director of YIAGA Africa, Samson Itodo, said this in a telephone interview with The PUNCH from Akure. Itodo said, “Subsequent off-cycle elections will be used as an opportunity to test new innovations for the 2023 elections. Edo will influence political behaviour of voters because it appears votes are beginning to count in elections. Nigeria may witness growth in voter turnout if the Ondo election is free, fair, credible, inclusive and safe. “Indeed, the Edo governorship election has set a new template for elections in Nigeria. Edo is a testament that votes can count in Nigerian elections; if institutions are given the opportunity to perform their functions without interference, they can deliver credible and nonviolent elections.” ir faces, and they have been in severe pains since then. They have launched a series of tirades against organised labour.” Copyright PUNCH.
